The paper deals with the design and analysis of polar codes with memory, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the implementation of hardware decoders, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AR (Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves simulations and analysis of the performance of the proposed codes, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
